Boil a full #kettle{}.

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and remove the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips. Trim then halve the @carrot{1}, then slice into 1cm thick rounds (no need to peel). Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @British beef mince{240%g}, carrot and sliced pepper. Fry until browned and tender, ~{7-8%minutes}. Use a spoon to break up the mince as it cooks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Meanwhile, pour the boiled water into a medium #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} on high heat.

Add the @egg noodle nests{125%g} and cook until tender, ~{4%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and run under cold water to stop them sticking together.

Once the mince is cooked, drain and discard any excess fat.

> IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Add the @Indonesian style spice mix{1%sachet}, @ginger puree{15%g} and garlic and cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @ketjap manis{50%g}, @soy sauce{15%ml}, @honey{15%g} and @water{50%ml}.

Bring to the boil, then simmer, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

When the sauce has thickened, add the cooked noodles.

Stir to coat the noodles in the sauce and cook until piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Taste and season with @salt and @ground black pepper if needed. Add a splash more water if the noodles look a little dry.

Share the beef noodles between your #bowls{}.

Finish by sprinkling over the @roasted white sesame seeds{5%g}.

Enjoy!